London Metal Exchange Hires Moelis as Strategic Adviser, FT Says

-- B y   R o b   S h e r i d a n
-- 
2011-09-17T11:29:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-17/london-metal-exchange-hires-moelis-as-strategic-adviser-ft-says.html
The London Metal Exchange hired
U.S.-based investment bank Moelis & Co., the Financial Times
reported today, citing people familiar with the matter it didn’t
identify.  Martin Abbott , chief executive officer of the LME, wants
Moelis and Managing Director Caroline Silver to advise on the
exchange’s “strategic options,” the newspaper said.  Calls to the exchange for comment were unreturned.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Robert Sheridan in London at 
 rsheridan6@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dick Schumacher at 
 dschumacher@bloomberg.net  